npth
------------------------------------------
nPth is a non-preemptive threads implementation using an API very similar
to the one known from GNU Pth.  It has been designed as a replacement of
GNU Pth for non-ancient operating systems.  In contrast to GNU Pth is is
based on the system's standard threads implementation.  Thus nPth allows
the use of libraries which are not compatible to GNU Pth.

Runtime requirements:
  bash-4.1.17-9
  cygwin-1.7.34-6
  libnpth0-1.1-1bl1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-9-1
  binutils-2.25-1
  cygport-0.17.1-1
  gcc-core-4.9.2-2
  libtool-2.4.2-5
  make-4.0-2

Canonical website:
  ftp://ftp.gnupg.org/gcrypt/npth/

Canonical download:
  ftp://ftp.gnupg.org/gcrypt/npth/npth-1.1.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack npth-1.1-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./npth-1.1-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/npth-1.1-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/npth-1.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libnpth0-1.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libnpth-devel-1.1-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(npth)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/npth.README
  /usr/share/doc/npth/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/npth/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/npth/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/npth/HACKING
  /usr/share/doc/npth/NEWS
  /usr/share/doc/npth/README

(libnpth0)
  /usr/bin/cygnpth-0.dll

(libnpth-devel)
  /usr/bin/npth-config
  /usr/include/npth.h
  /usr/lib/libnpth.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/npth.pc
  /usr/share/aclocal/npth.m4
  /usr/share/man/man1/npth-config.1.gz

